#. <section class="sutta" id="sn56.54"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.54:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.54:0.2"
msgid "6. Abhisamayavagga"
msgstr "6. Comprehension"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn56.54:0.3"
msgid "54. Dutiyasambhejjasutta"
msgstr "54. Where the Waters Flow Together (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.54:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yatthimā mahānadiyo saṃsandanti samenti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, there are places where the great rivers—the Ganges, Yamuna, "
"Aciravatī, Sarabhū, and Mahī—come together and converge."

msgctxt "sn56.54:1.2"
msgid ""
"gaṅgā, yamunā, aciravatī, sarabhū, mahī, taṃ udakaṃ parikkhayaṃ pariyādānaṃ "
"gaccheyya, ṭhapetvā dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni."
msgstr ""
"Suppose that water dried up and evaporated except for two or three drops."

msgctxt "sn56.54:1.3"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn56.54:1.4"
msgid ""
"katamaṃ nu kho bahutaraṃ—yaṃ vā saṃbhejjaudakaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādinnaṃ, "
"yāni dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni avasiṭṭhānī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Which is more: the water in the confluence that has dried up and evaporated, "
"or the two or three drops left?”"

msgctxt "sn56.54:1.5"
msgid ""
"“Etadeva, bhante, bahutaraṃ saṃbhejjaudakaṃ yadidaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādinnaṃ;"
" appamattakāni dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni avasiṭṭhāni."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, the water in the confluence that has dried up and evaporated is "
"certainly more. The two or three drops left are tiny."

msgctxt "sn56.54:1.6"
msgid ""
"Saṅkhampi na upenti, upanidhampi na upenti, kalabhāgampi na upenti "
"saṃbhejjaudakaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ pariyādinnaṃ upanidhāya dve vā tīṇi vā "
"udakaphusitāni avasiṭṭhānī”ti."
msgstr ""
"Compared to the water in the confluence that has dried up and evaporated, it "
"can’t be reckoned or compared, it’s not even a fraction.”"

msgctxt "sn56.54:1.7"
msgid "“Evameva kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa … pe …"
msgstr "“In the same way, for a noble disciple …"

msgctxt "sn56.54:1.8"
msgid "yogo karaṇīyo”ti."
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.54:1.9"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
